      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Race for No. 2: A Debate With a Difference</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Michael David Smith letter, commenting on October 6 article, says Reform and Green Party candidates should have participated in vice presidential debate between Sen Joseph I Lieberman and rival Dick Cheney</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>While I watched the vice-presidential debate between Joseph I. Lieberman and Dick Cheney on Thursday (front page, Oct. 6), one thought kept creeping into my mind: this would be much more interesting if the Reform and Green Party candidates were taking part.</p>
        <p>MICHAEL DAVID SMITH  Long Beach, Calif., Oct. 6, 2000</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>While I watched the vice-presidential debate between Joseph I. Lieberman and Dick Cheney on Thursday (front page, Oct. 6), one thought kept creeping into my mind: this would be much more interesting if the Reform and Green Party candidates were taking part.</p>
        <p>MICHAEL DAVID SMITH  Long Beach, Calif., Oct. 6, 2000</p>
